==Function==
In biographies of Swiss parliamentarians (members of the [[Swiss National Council]] or the [[Swiss Council of States]]), this template may be used to link to the corresponding profile on website of the Swiss parliament, usually under the "References" or "External links" heading.

The outline of the profile is generally in the main language of the parliamentarian (German, French, Italian, or Romansh), even on the English language version of the website.

==Usage==
'''<nowiki>{{Parliament.ch|ID|AlternateName|date=}}</nowiki>'''

where ''ID'' is the ID number of the profile. The ID number is apparent in the [[URL]], for example ''<nowiki>http://www.parlament.ch/E/Suche/Pages/biografie.aspx?biografie_id=</nowiki>'''267'''''.

The parameter ''AlternateName'' is optional, but if used must immediately follow the ID. When used, this name will appear as the name of the parliamentarian. Otherwise, the article name will appear.

The parameter ''date='' is optional. When supplied with the date of the retrieval of the profile in [[ISO 8601]] YYYY-MM-DD format, e.g. ''2007-12-03'', it appends version information to the reference. The date text must not be wikilinked.

==Examples==
*When used in the article [[Samuel Schmid]]<br>
'''<nowiki>{{Parliament.ch|267}}</nowiki>'''<br>
results in:<br>
{{Parliament.ch|267|Samuel Schmid}}

*But in the same article<br>
'''<nowiki>{{Parliament.ch|267|Samuel Schmid (Bern)}}</nowiki>'''<br>
would result in:<br>
{{Parliament.ch|267|Samuel Schmid (Bern)}}

*Using the date:
'''<nowiki>{{Parliament.ch|267|Samuel Schmid|date=2006-08-13}}</nowiki>'''<br>
results in:<br>
{{Parliament.ch|267|Samuel Schmid|date=2006-08-13}}
